rdf:Description.lla:note: Lewis Lewis was sick and left in the hospital at Port Said on 8th October 1868. Griffith Williams, the mate, took over as master until Lewis rejoined the ship at Dunkirk on 5th Feb 1869. Near collision with a French Brig (Marechal Erelmas?) on 9th December 1868. The jib of the French ship ripped away the main sail of the Glenara and caused other damage.
Temporary promotion to master when Lewis Lewis was hospitalised in Port Said in October 1868. Griffith Williams remained as master until Lewis rejoined the ship in Dunkirk on 5th Feb 1869.
